  "text": "The treatments for subgroups 1 and 2, are delivered in primary care by NHS physiotherapists. Participants continue to be able to access other care via their GP. The physiotherapists treating patients in subgroups 1 and 2 are responsible for providing good clinical governance to their patients and will be permitted to overrule the stratification algorithm recommendation for matched care pathways, if they strongly believe this is necessary. As in our previous trials [CITATION_1] , such protocol deviations are expected to be rare and will always be discussed with the treating physiotherapist's spinal specialist mentor and the trial principal investigator (PI), and documented.",
